# Security headers for the Central Command SPA on Cloudflare Pages.
#
# Pages only serves this file on deployed builds (production + preview), which
# are always HTTPS — so Strict-Transport-Security and upgrade-insecure-requests
# are safe here. The local dev loop runs `vite dev`, which does NOT read this
# file, so WebKit/Safari never sees HSTS against http://localhost (the known
# gotcha where it rewrites localhost requests to https and breaks dev).
#
# CSP allow-list notes (every source is something the app actually loads):
#   script-src 'self'      theme-init.js + the Vite bundle are same-origin; the
#                          theme bootstrap was moved out of index.html to keep
#                          this strict (no 'unsafe-inline').
#   style-src  'unsafe-inline'  React/SVG set style via element attributes;
#                          there is no inline <style> or CSS-in-JS to nonce.
#   img-src    https:      news thumbnails come from arbitrary RSS image hosts
#                          (ESPN, Hacker News, TechCrunch, PCGamesN, Dexerto).
#   connect-src 'self'     the API is same-origin (/api/* on the same host;
#                          Vite proxies /api in dev). No cross-origin fetches.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
